 "<p>gzscene's init function automatically adds a light and a grid to the scene:</p>\n<p><a href=\"#!/osrf/gzweb/src/576579ae7349b026e1d2f592c93ac6bf07891461/gz3d/src/gzscene.js?at=default&amp;fileviewer=file-view-default#gzscene.js-41\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#!/osrf/gzweb/src/576579ae7349b026e1d2f592c93ac6bf07891461/gz3d/src/gzscene.js?at=default&amp;fileviewer=file-view-default#gzscene.js-41</a></p>\n<p>As we move towards more reusable code, the scene should be initialized empty by default, and it is up to each application to add things to it.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2017-11-17T18:03:02.505076+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2017-11-20T03:31:19.958008+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 137}